256
00:15:56,030 --> 00:16:02,690
♫ <i>Let me go and my life</i> ♫

257
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:16,100
I'm sorry, Jung Shin.

258
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:18,820
I'm sorry.

259
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,810
Why are you sorry to me?

260
00:16:22,810 --> 00:16:25,660
What are you sorry about?

261
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:27,620
All of it.

262
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:30,260
I'm sorry about everything.

263
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:36,740
Why did you do that!

264
00:16:36,740 --> 00:16:38,770
Why did you do that to that poor guy!

265
00:16:38,770 --> 00:16:40,880
Why did you do that...

266
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:44,300
Why did you do that, Cheol Woong...

267
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:48,920
You read it, too.

268
00:16:48,920 --> 00:16:51,150
His dream was to become a Korean Literature teacher.

269
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:54,300
He dreamed of living together with me.

270
00:16:54,300 --> 00:16:56,950
But he says that was a ridiculous ambition and a useless dream!

271
00:16:56,950 --> 00:16:58,970
It's something everyone else could achieve!

272
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:02,900
How is that anything big or something to dream about!

273
00:17:04,610 --> 00:17:08,800
He says it was a dream he should never have dreamed as the son of a servant.

274
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:11,510
I was scared

275
00:17:12,510 --> 00:17:14,660
that my life would end.

276
00:17:15,970 --> 00:17:18,560
Most importantly,

277
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:22,090
I was most afraid of not being able to see you again.

278
00:17:23,370 --> 00:17:25,100
I'm sorry, Jung Shin.

279
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:28,450
I really wanted to be a decent guy to you.

280
00:17:34,810 --> 00:17:36,580
Then, what about Doo Hak?

281
00:17:37,530 --> 00:17:39,650
It's okay for Doo Hak's life to end?

282
00:17:39,650 --> 00:17:42,350
Is that why you killed Doo Hak's father as well?

283
00:17:42,350 --> 00:17:45,300
No, that's really not true, Jung Shin.

284
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:48,700
Doo Hak's father was really like a father to me, too.

285
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:51,500
How could I do that to someone I considered a father?

286
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:54,660
That was really an accident.

287
00:17:54,660 --> 00:17:56,930
I did my best to look into it.

288
00:17:56,930 --> 00:17:58,840
Now, I can't believe anything you say anymore.

289
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:01,860
Jung Shin, I'm tormented, too!

290
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:06,650
I have done so up to this point,

291
00:18:06,650 --> 00:18:08,860
but I will keep living...

292
00:18:08,860 --> 00:18:11,680
to atone for what I did.

293
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:15,740
Leave.

294
00:18:17,180 --> 00:18:20,330
Killing that bastard in Yeosu...

295
00:18:20,330 --> 00:18:22,160
That was your fault.

296
00:18:23,050 --> 00:18:28,450
I was able to endure him taking my money and beating me,

297
00:18:28,450 --> 00:18:31,550
but when that bastard hit you, I really

298
00:18:31,550 --> 00:18:34,070
wanted to kill him.

299
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:37,230
Jung Shin,

300
00:18:37,230 --> 00:18:40,120
it's true that I was wrong,

301
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:42,630
but I can't turn back.

302
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,530
Just...

303
00:18:47,950 --> 00:18:51,940
I-I'll just be good to you.

304
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:56,450
I'll be good to you and Ahjumma severalfold to make up for Doo Hak hyung.

305
00:18:56,450 --> 00:18:58,200
Choi Cheol Woong...

306
00:19:02,340 --> 00:19:05,510
I don't know if I can stand to see you anymore.

307
00:19:06,610 --> 00:19:08,710
Don't call me again.

308
00:19:26,370 --> 00:19:33,390
♫ <i>Will I be able to come to you again?</i> ♫

309
00:19:33,390 --> 00:19:40,300
♫ <i>Trembling eyes, they're even more sorrowful</i> ♫

310
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:47,640
♫ <i>Above the rough sky, my heart floats away</i> ♫

311
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:55,810
♫ <i>Only your name, I engrave like this</i> ♫

312
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,480
Cheol Woong...

313
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:11,520
When did you come home?

314
00:20:12,650 --> 00:20:15,170
You must be tired, wash up and go to bed early–

315
00:20:22,990 --> 00:20:24,480
What's wrong with your hand?

316
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:26,820
How did you get hurt?

317
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:33,720
The skin on your knuckles have all peeled off!

318
00:20:35,890 --> 00:20:36,970
Just wait a moment.

319
00:20:36,970 --> 00:20:39,220
I will bring ointment.

320
00:20:39,220 --> 00:20:41,190
Mom.

321
00:20:41,190 --> 00:20:42,770
Yeah?

322
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:49,490
Why did you raise me like this?

323
00:20:50,490 --> 00:20:52,530
What do you mean?

324
00:20:59,130 --> 00:21:01,160
What happened?

325
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:03,680
If I did something wrong,

326
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:08,690
you should have scolded me and hit me with a stick.

327
00:21:08,690 --> 00:21:13,130
You should have punished me until I was remorseful.

328
00:21:13,130 --> 00:21:14,880
Cheol Woong...

329
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:18,390
why are you being like that?

330
00:21:18,390 --> 00:21:21,660
I even killed someone!

331
00:21:21,660 --> 00:21:24,280
So how did you manage to do that, Mom?

332
00:21:25,630 --> 00:21:29,100
Even if I begged you to save me,

333
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:31,960
y-you should've had me pay the price

334
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:36,200
so that I grow up, live properly,

335
00:21:36,210 --> 00:21:39,310
and come to my senses, Mom.

336
00:21:41,630 --> 00:21:46,230
Doo Hak hyung's life was ruined, and he died because of me.

337
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:50,250
Ahjussi died, too.

338
00:21:50,250 --> 00:21:54,730
After that, there was never a day I felt at peace.

339
00:21:55,730 --> 00:21:57,290
Mom,

340
00:21:58,190 --> 00:22:01,500
if you'd sent me to jail instead of protecting me,

341
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:04,260
will things be different now?

342
00:22:04,260 --> 00:22:06,980
Cheol Woong, don't be like this.

343
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:11,110
You are my everything.

344
00:22:11,110 --> 00:22:14,520
If I had sent you to prison then, I would

345
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:16,710
probably be dead.

346
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:19,670
For you,

347
00:22:19,670 --> 00:22:23,110
I could do even worse things.

348
00:22:23,110 --> 00:22:25,300
If I could just save you,

349
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:29,090
I could even give up my heart! You're...

350
00:22:29,090 --> 00:22:31,860
You are my life.

351
00:22:37,290 --> 00:22:39,380
You're right.

352
00:22:39,380 --> 00:22:41,210
I...

353
00:22:41,210 --> 00:22:42,370
I'm your life.

354
00:22:42,370 --> 00:22:44,210
Yeah. That's right.

355
00:22:44,210 --> 00:22:46,230
So...

356
00:22:46,230 --> 00:22:47,800
Mom,

357
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:51,330
you lived for yourself,

358
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:54,380
not for me.

359
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:58,880
Cheol Woong.

360
00:23:00,010 --> 00:23:02,160
Why are you being like this?

361
00:23:02,160 --> 00:23:06,020
What took place that you're being like this?

362
00:23:07,020 --> 00:23:09,140
Jung Shin...

363
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:14,810
found out...

364
00:23:17,870 --> 00:23:19,800
that I'm a murderer.

365
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:22,640
How?

366
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:25,960
How could she know?

367
00:23:28,530 --> 00:23:31,000
I told her, Mom.

368
00:23:32,580 --> 00:23:34,120
Cheol Woong!

369
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:37,110
What have you done!

370
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:38,960
Mom.

371
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:41,910
I can't hold it in anymore.

372
00:23:41,910 --> 00:23:45,670
I just can't deal with this anymore!

373
00:23:47,540 --> 00:23:50,640
I'm sick of acting like I'm okay,

374
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:53,470
and like I'm not the one.

375
00:23:54,470 --> 00:23:58,910
Doo Hak hyung ruined his entire life because of me!

376
00:23:58,910 --> 00:24:02,010
It's same as if I killed him!

377
00:24:03,010 --> 00:24:04,780
Not only that,

378
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:13,800
Jung Shin even says she will leave me.

379
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:15,770
No, no!

380
00:24:16,790 --> 00:24:18,960
What do I do, Mom?

381
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:27,880
Don't worry, Cheol Woong.

382
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:33,360
I will...

383
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:36,320
meet Jung Shin and shut her mouth.

384
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:40,600
She won't ever report you or anything like that. Actually,

385
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:43,080
even if she were to report you,

386
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:47,830
Doo Hak has already served the full sentence and died!

387
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:51,200
So what could possibly happen?

388
00:24:56,020 --> 00:24:57,590
It's okay.

389
00:24:59,150 --> 00:25:00,700
It's okay.

390
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:02,400
It's okay.

391
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:25,600
How did you endure that?

392
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:29,350
How? You idiot!

393
00:25:31,310 --> 00:25:33,680
It's because you were there, Jung Shin.

394
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:35,160
Because of you.

395
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:47,440
He said he had nothing to do with your father's death.

396
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:49,530
Of course, he would.

397
00:25:49,530 --> 00:25:52,550
It was his last chance to seem human to you.

398
00:25:52,550 --> 00:25:55,560
No. That part seemed truthful.

399
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:58,520
You hope it was the truth.

400
00:25:58,520 --> 00:26:00,290
Doo Hak,

401
00:26:00,290 --> 00:26:02,630
can't you just end it here?

402
00:26:02,630 --> 00:26:05,510
You can't go back to the way things were anyway.

403
00:26:05,510 --> 00:26:08,360
You should visit your mother and find Jung Ok,

404
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:12,150
and let's go to the U.S. or Japan and live there.

405
00:26:12,150 --> 00:26:15,480
You should spend the rest of your life like a human being.

406
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:19,370
I know.

407
00:26:19,370 --> 00:26:20,940
We should leave.

408
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:26,880
- Do you really mean that? 
 - I'm not interested in revenge or getting justice.

409
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:29,460
The reason why I fought with my life to return

410
00:26:29,460 --> 00:26:32,080
was to meet you again.

411
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:35,340
I thought I would be okay with everything being forgotten

412
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:39,540
if I could just be happy with you.

413
00:26:40,540 --> 00:26:42,940
But every night,

414
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:46,370
my heart is engulfed in flames

415
00:26:47,370 --> 00:26:49,840
and burns up my entire body.

416
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:54,990
I don't know how to describe it.

417
00:26:57,730 --> 00:27:00,070
Jung Shin.

418
00:27:00,070 --> 00:27:02,050
I need to quench those flames.

419
00:27:02,050 --> 00:27:05,120
If not, I would burn to death from those flames even if I leave this country!

420
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:08,280
And those flames will spread to you, too.

421
00:27:08,280 --> 00:27:10,560
I'm scared.

422
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:12,840
I'm so scared that I'll go mad.

423
00:27:30,750 --> 00:27:32,500
All right.

424
00:27:32,500 --> 00:27:35,590
Let's quench those flames together.

425
00:27:41,060 --> 00:27:43,610
But in return, promise me...

426
00:27:43,610 --> 00:27:46,300
that you will not burn up in those flames.

427
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:49,510
Jung Shin...

428
00:27:50,790 --> 00:27:52,800
Let's do it together, Doo Hak.

429
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:55,790
We can do it together.

430
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:32,000
♫ <i>Somebody please tell me now, what am I supposed to do?</i> ♫

431
00:28:34,650 --> 00:28:42,210
♫ <i>Maybe you'll come lie to me now, what am I supposed to do?</i> ♫

432
00:28:44,870 --> 00:28:50,010
♫ <i>Must have been fallen, must have been done</i> ♫

433
00:28:50,010 --> 00:28:55,040
♫ <i>Darling, it's all in your mind</i> ♫

434
00:28:55,040 --> 00:29:00,180
♫ <i>I will come back, Darling, have me back</i> ♫

435
00:29:00,180 --> 00:29:03,260
♫ <i>And hear me</i> ♫

436
00:29:04,990 --> 00:29:10,520
♫ <i>They charge for the darkness and dart for the rhythm</i> ♫

437
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:15,820
♫ <i>And then you are lost in your mind</i> ♫

438
00:29:15,820 --> 00:29:17,820
Did you sleep well?

439
00:29:18,890 --> 00:29:20,460
Yeah.

440
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:28,080
♫ <i>Kill me softly</i> ♫

441
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:30,870
Thanks for being alive, Doo Hak.

442
00:29:34,570 --> 00:29:36,860
It took me too long.

443
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:42,300
My heart was tearing apart much more when we met again

444
00:29:42,360 --> 00:29:46,100
than when we were separated.

445
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,250
Afraid that it might be a dream

446
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:54,190
and that I might wake up from the dream.

447
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:56,780
If this is a dream,

448
00:29:56,780 --> 00:29:59,320
then let's not ever wake up.

449
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:06,230
♫ <i>Please do, somebody</i> ♫

450
00:30:06,230 --> 00:30:13,530
♫ <i>Breathe in, nobody knows</i> ♫

451
00:30:13,550 --> 00:30:18,350
♫ <i>Nobody knows, the pain</i> ♫

452
00:30:20,450 --> 00:30:22,950
You're here, Mother?

453
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:27,380
- Ta-da!
- Whoa!

454
00:30:28,210 --> 00:30:30,630
Oh, my goodness. What is all this?

455
00:30:30,630 --> 00:30:33,660
Well, this is your first time coming to my house.

456
00:30:33,660 --> 00:30:37,960
Even so, it's a housewarming, not a birthday party.

457
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:41,250
Huh? Is it a special occasion today?

458
00:30:41,250 --> 00:30:42,310
Yes.

459
00:30:42,310 --> 00:30:45,460
Housewarmings and birthdays aren't the only special occasions.

460
00:30:45,460 --> 00:30:48,810
If the day was peaceful without any trouble, that's also a special occasion.

461
00:30:48,810 --> 00:30:53,500
My, you sound like a grandma who's lived a century.

462
00:30:54,510 --> 00:30:57,830
Anyhow, it feels great to see you.

463
00:30:57,830 --> 00:30:59,520
Me, too.

464
00:30:59,520 --> 00:31:02,250
All right, now. Let's close our eyes and say our wishes.

465
00:31:02,250 --> 00:31:04,040
Shall we?

466
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:04,410
Jung Shin...

467
00:32:04,410 --> 00:32:07,310
I'm hallucinating here.

468
00:32:07,310 --> 00:32:09,900
I see Doo Hak right now.

469
00:32:12,130 --> 00:32:15,920
I must really be close to my death now.

470
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:22,050
Mom...

471
00:32:22,050 --> 00:32:23,850
Oh, my.

472
00:32:23,850 --> 00:32:27,550
He even called me just now.

473
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:29,480
It is Doo Hak.

474
00:32:30,330 --> 00:32:33,190
He came back alive. He did.

475
00:32:37,620 --> 00:32:40,610
What's the matter with you?

476
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:46,800
Mom, I'm Doo Hak.

477
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:48,760
Your son...

478
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:57,080
Mom, I'm really sorry.

479
00:33:38,750 --> 00:33:40,500
Aigoo...

480
00:33:40,500 --> 00:33:42,980
I-Is it you, Doo Hak?

481
00:33:42,980 --> 00:33:44,620
M-My baby...

482
00:33:44,620 --> 00:33:47,380
Are you my baby, D-Doo Hak?

483
00:33:47,380 --> 00:33:48,790
Yes.

484
00:33:50,090 --> 00:33:52,550
Mom, I'm sorry.

485
00:34:05,830 --> 00:34:08,400
I'm really sorry, Mom.

486
00:34:22,850 --> 00:34:25,630
My baby!

487
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:28,180
Lying together likes this...

488
00:34:28,180 --> 00:34:32,610
reminds me of the days when we all slept in one room.

489
00:34:36,250 --> 00:34:38,140
Mom...

490
00:34:39,140 --> 00:34:42,330
aren't there any countries you want to visit?

491
00:34:42,330 --> 00:34:43,500
Why wouldn't there be?

492
00:34:43,500 --> 00:34:46,060
I never even got to ride an airplane.

493
00:34:46,820 --> 00:34:49,310
Why? Are you going to buy me a trip around the world?

494
00:34:49,310 --> 00:34:52,310
Gosh, you think that's all I can do for you?

495
00:34:52,310 --> 00:34:54,390
Whether it's the U.S. or the U.K.,

496
00:34:54,390 --> 00:34:57,340
you can just go and live there.

497
00:35:00,740 --> 00:35:04,210
Is it because living in Korea is a bit difficult...

498
00:35:04,210 --> 00:35:07,100
that you want to go live abroad?

499
00:35:08,930 --> 00:35:11,310
Well, that's part of it.

500
00:35:15,150 --> 00:35:16,800
Doo Hak...

501
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:20,420
I'm fine with wherever.

502
00:35:20,420 --> 00:35:25,380
If I can just live with my child in this old age...

503
00:35:25,380 --> 00:35:28,000
wouldn't that be my hometown?

504
00:35:36,410 --> 00:35:38,500
Okay, Mom.

505
00:35:38,500 --> 00:35:40,590
By the way...

506
00:35:40,590 --> 00:35:43,050
I just have one request for you.

507
00:35:45,940 --> 00:35:48,680
Don't ever be a bad son again.

508
00:35:50,050 --> 00:35:53,490
You should never pass on before your parents.

509
00:35:54,510 --> 00:35:57,190
And don't pretend to be dead, either.

510
00:35:58,470 --> 00:36:00,350
Do you understand?

511
00:36:02,950 --> 00:36:04,790
Yes, Mom.

512
00:36:06,630 --> 00:36:08,960
Thank you, my baby.

513
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:13,820
Today is really your birthday.

514
00:36:15,050 --> 00:36:18,190
It's better than the day I gave birth to you.

515
00:36:19,190 --> 00:36:20,670
Gosh.

516
00:36:21,910 --> 00:36:23,470
Aigoo!

517
00:36:27,430 --> 00:36:28,660
Please make the preparations right away.

518
00:36:28,660 --> 00:36:30,850
Yes, right on.

519
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:36,630
Hello, Madam.

520
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:40,550
What brings you here, so early in the morning?

521
00:36:41,450 --> 00:36:45,280
I brought an important information for you.

522
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:48,500
If you aren't interested, I'll take my leave.

523
00:36:50,250 --> 00:36:51,830
Do you...

524
00:36:51,830 --> 00:36:54,030
want a separate reward again?

525
00:36:54,030 --> 00:36:55,890
How could I?

526
00:36:55,890 --> 00:36:57,750
So...

527
00:36:57,750 --> 00:37:00,120
what is this information you speak of?

528
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:03,350
Changsung Group's situation is worse than expected.

529
00:37:03,350 --> 00:37:08,510
Even our agency is worried they might go bankrupt.

530
00:37:09,510 --> 00:37:13,210
I thought that was why they wanted Choi Cheol Woong.

531
00:37:13,210 --> 00:37:15,250
But that wasn't the case.

532
00:37:15,250 --> 00:37:17,490
We were fooled.

533
00:37:18,490 --> 00:37:22,860
They already knew Choi Cheol Woong likes Oh Jung Shin.

534
00:37:22,860 --> 00:37:26,010
Why'd they pull off such a show, then?

535
00:37:27,350 --> 00:37:30,590
It's all for the Sooseo District Development business.

536
00:37:30,590 --> 00:37:33,630
How much did he say the profit was?

537
00:37:35,030 --> 00:37:38,810
I assume he probably said something like 100 billion won.

538
00:37:38,810 --> 00:37:40,560
In fact...

539
00:37:40,560 --> 00:37:42,900
it's at least 500 billion won.

540
00:37:42,900 --> 00:37:45,180
He lowered the profit when telling his partners,

541
00:37:45,180 --> 00:37:47,320
in an attempt to take the rest for himself.

542
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:52,460
Additionally, he desperately needs you and Deputy Director for that business at the moment.

543
00:37:53,970 --> 00:37:55,590
How did you find out about this?

544
00:37:55,590 --> 00:38:00,300
Well, our company's work involves keeping a watch on corporations.

545
00:38:00,300 --> 00:38:02,060
If there's anything else you want to confirm,

546
00:38:02,060 --> 00:38:04,180
- tell Deputy Director—
- No.

547
00:38:04,180 --> 00:38:07,260
He doesn't know about my deal with Chairman Keum.

548
00:38:12,430 --> 00:38:15,520
But this isn't necessarily a bad news.

549
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:18,730
It's wrong for Chairman Keum to have fooled you.

550
00:38:18,730 --> 00:38:20,540
But your profit is...

551
00:38:20,540 --> 00:38:23,880
also increasing as a result, isn't it?

552
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:26,230
And mine as well.

553
00:38:28,810 --> 00:38:30,930
I must meet Chairman Keum.

554
00:38:30,930 --> 00:38:33,170
No. Even if you meet him now...

555
00:38:33,170 --> 00:38:37,310
he'll deny it, showing you the financial forecast.

556
00:38:37,310 --> 00:38:39,260
Only after the business has been accomplished,

557
00:38:39,260 --> 00:38:41,220
that's when you must strike him.

558
00:38:41,220 --> 00:38:46,320
We must also prepare a surefire evidence he can't deny in the meantime.

559
00:38:47,320 --> 00:38:52,000
That's how you'll be able to get your fair share.

560
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:53,940
Do you understand?

561
00:39:20,390 --> 00:39:22,670
It's out of ammo.

562
00:39:22,670 --> 00:39:25,530
Stop playing around and kill me right now.

563
00:39:25,530 --> 00:39:28,910
I don't like playing with a person's life, either.

564
00:39:28,910 --> 00:39:32,350
But there's one thing I'm sincerely curious about.

565
00:39:32,350 --> 00:39:35,380
There was another person who wanted to kill you besides me.

566
00:39:35,380 --> 00:39:38,310
Cut the bullshit.

567
00:39:43,850 --> 00:39:46,570
<i>What? You want me to kill a person?</i>

568
00:39:46,570 --> 00:39:48,560
<i>Who's this request from?</i>

569
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:49,710
I don't know about that.

570
00:39:49,710 --> 00:39:52,860
He only left the documents in the mail.

571
00:39:52,860 --> 00:39:55,480
But why would he come to me?

572
00:39:58,290 --> 00:40:00,320
I mean, you told me to bring you

573
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:02,930
anything that will make money after you got out of jail.

574
00:40:02,930 --> 00:40:04,830
Come on, now! Even so,

575
00:40:04,830 --> 00:40:06,810
am I a human butcher or something?

576
00:40:06,810 --> 00:40:09,060
Gosh, Hyungnim, your knife skills are neat, aren't they?

577
00:40:09,060 --> 00:40:12,730
Man, that's only when we're at an all out war.

578
00:40:12,730 --> 00:40:15,330
How could I kill a complete stranger?

579
00:40:15,330 --> 00:40:17,120
Aigoo, seriously, this guy.

580
00:40:17,120 --> 00:40:19,110
Just forget about it!

581
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:21,400
Aigoo, all right.

582
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:24,000
I'll look for something else. Let's go.

583
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,220
<i>How much are they paying?</i>

584
00:40:25,220 --> 00:40:28,010
<i>One hundred million won upfront and 200 million won after the job is done.</i>

585
00:40:28,010 --> 00:40:29,930
<i>What? Three hundred million won?</i>

586
00:40:29,930 --> 00:40:31,250
<i>Yes.</i>

587
00:40:31,250 --> 00:40:32,600
<i>Who do they want?</i>

588
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:34,750
<i>The name is Oh Man Ok.</i>

589
00:40:34,750 --> 00:40:36,760
<i>He's in the NSA, apparently.</i>

590
00:40:40,510 --> 00:40:43,130
You know what's so funny?

591
00:40:43,130 --> 00:40:46,550
The one who got the request is pretty close to us.

592
00:40:46,550 --> 00:40:49,770
So he came to consult us about what  to do.

593
00:40:49,770 --> 00:40:51,260
Isn't it funny?

594
00:40:51,260 --> 00:40:52,960
You think...

595
00:40:52,960 --> 00:40:56,560
I'd be fooled by such tricks?

596
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:57,800
Hurry up and finish.

597
00:40:57,800 --> 00:41:00,480
I'm not playing tricks.

598
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:01,980
You're my sworn enemy.

599
00:41:01,980 --> 00:41:04,920
So I want to kill you right away. However...

600
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:07,550
I'm really just curious.

601
00:41:07,550 --> 00:41:09,790
Don't you have anyone in mind?

602
00:41:09,790 --> 00:41:12,330
I don't know, you asshole.

603
00:41:13,330 --> 00:41:16,440
Don't be like that and use your brain a little more.

604
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:18,550
Don't play both sides against the middle.

605
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:22,790
By that, you mean...

606
00:41:22,790 --> 00:41:25,460
it's someone who's close to you, huh?

607
00:41:27,290 --> 00:41:28,870
Oh Man Ok...

608
00:41:29,870 --> 00:41:35,050
will you be able to sleep at night if there exists someone who knows

609
00:41:35,050 --> 00:41:38,050
everything about you, including your flaws?

610
00:41:38,050 --> 00:41:40,880
If you'll help us out...

611
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:44,880
you can have all the money that the person you're suspecting owns.

612
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:49,460
I'll get my revenge against the one who's trying to kill you...

613
00:41:49,460 --> 00:41:50,980
and you become rich.

614
00:41:50,980 --> 00:41:53,600
Isn't it a once-in-a-lifetime chance?

615
00:41:53,600 --> 00:41:55,790
<i>Think about it carefully.</i>

616
00:42:05,740 --> 00:42:07,190
<i>Kang Yeo Jin...</i>

617
00:42:07,190 --> 00:42:09,210
<i>Choi Cheol Woong...</i>

618
00:42:09,210 --> 00:42:11,520
<i>You two really did it?</i>

619
00:42:17,310 --> 00:42:20,530
[Choonmoo-si: became modern-day Tongyeong-si after consolidation of administrative districts in 1995.]

620
00:42:20,640 --> 00:42:22,510
You're Park Dae Sung's hoobae from high school?

621
00:42:22,510 --> 00:42:23,480
Yes, Sunbaenim!

622
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:27,280
Gosh, Park Dae Sung's living the good life, isn't he?

623
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:30,760
[Kim Sung  Yeob: Prosecutor of Choongmoo-si's Criminal Investigation Team]
He was right on starting his own office, quitting the prosecutor job.

624
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:33,470
He makes good money and got a great wife.

625
00:42:33,470 --> 00:42:36,110
Aigoo, I'm so jealous.

626
00:42:36,110 --> 00:42:37,710
I'm jealous.

627
00:42:37,710 --> 00:42:41,330
Please speak comfortably*, Sunbaenim.
(Skip the honorifics)

628
00:42:41,330 --> 00:42:43,040
Should I?

629
00:42:44,350 --> 00:42:46,130
All right. What brings you all the way here?

630
00:42:46,130 --> 00:42:48,600
You didn't come to ask me favor...

631
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:50,170
or something like that, right?

632
00:42:50,170 --> 00:42:53,130
Gosh, even though I'm a prosecutor...

633
00:42:53,130 --> 00:42:55,460
my sword is all rusty and worn-out.

634
00:42:55,460 --> 00:42:57,520
It's falling apart into pieces.

635
00:42:57,520 --> 00:43:00,210
In one word, I have no power.

636
00:43:00,210 --> 00:43:02,760
Isn't it because you're too upright?

637
00:43:02,760 --> 00:43:04,350
Hey!

638
00:43:05,810 --> 00:43:07,770
All right. Say hi.

639
00:43:07,770 --> 00:43:10,570
The journalist you asked me to cast.

640
00:43:10,570 --> 00:43:13,890
He's the journalist, whom Chun Doo Hwan had fired when he consolidated

641
00:43:13,890 --> 00:43:15,680
all the news agencies back then.

642
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:17,580
He's a long-time drinking buddy of Director Go,

643
00:43:17,580 --> 00:43:20,750
whom he got to know because of the Ministry of Culture matter.

644
00:43:20,750 --> 00:43:21,830
I'd like to introduce myself.

645
00:43:21,830 --> 00:43:25,960
- I'm a film producer Oh Jung Shin.
- Oh, yes.

646
00:43:25,960 --> 00:43:29,260
My name is Shin Sik, and I run a small magazine publishing company.

647
00:43:29,260 --> 00:43:31,010
His name is Shin Sik*...
(Shinsik: newest style/trend in Korean)

648
00:43:31,010 --> 00:43:35,060
but his way of life is so stubborn and old-fashioned.

649
00:43:35,060 --> 00:43:37,610
Even when I tell him to just work for a news agency,

650
00:43:37,610 --> 00:43:41,360
he keeps talking about realizing true spirit of journalism

651
00:43:41,360 --> 00:43:46,290
with other journalists who also got fired, altogether starving to death.

652
00:43:47,270 --> 00:43:49,520
All right. What's your business?

653
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:53,820
In fact, I'm trying to run a resort around here.

654
00:43:53,820 --> 00:43:58,390
And when you run a business, complaints and arguments are sure to follow.

655
00:43:58,390 --> 00:43:59,840
That's for sure!

656
00:43:59,840 --> 00:44:02,110
So I came down in advance to get to know you while I'm at it.

657
00:44:02,110 --> 00:44:04,490
Getting to know each other is great!

658
00:44:04,490 --> 00:44:07,230
So, what do you have for me?

659
00:44:07,230 --> 00:44:10,190
First off, I'll give you 10 million won per month.

660
00:44:10,190 --> 00:44:13,390
And I'll take care of all expenses you incur.

661
00:44:13,390 --> 00:44:17,290
Also, I heard the house you have in Seoul is about 676 sq ft, on an annual lease.

662
00:44:17,290 --> 00:44:20,380
But it's a little small for your wife and kids to live in, right?

663
00:44:20,380 --> 00:44:22,160
If you get back to your position Seoul,

664
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:25,720
I'll buy you a 1,000 sq ft apartment in Gangnam.

665
00:44:25,720 --> 00:44:28,960
You've got a lot of money, my lad.

666
00:44:28,960 --> 00:44:31,540
Gosh, I guess this year is my year, huh?

667
00:44:31,540 --> 00:44:35,180
For such a great sponsor to come to befriend me!

668
00:44:35,180 --> 00:44:37,060
All right!

669
00:44:37,060 --> 00:44:39,740
Dear Sponsor Hoobanim, let's drink up.

670
00:44:39,740 --> 00:44:41,520
Yes, Sunbaenim!

671
00:44:46,050 --> 00:44:47,880
That's great.

672
00:44:49,290 --> 00:44:50,650
Please take a bite, Sunbaenim.

673
00:44:50,650 --> 00:44:53,680
Geez... No, no.

674
00:44:53,680 --> 00:44:56,720
There's something else I like more than sashimi.

675
00:44:56,720 --> 00:44:58,060
Sorry? Wh-What is that?

676
00:44:58,060 --> 00:45:00,150
- You can order anything you want!
- You f***!

677
00:45:02,860 --> 00:45:05,960
I just love this taste, you see?

678
00:45:05,960 --> 00:45:09,180
This flavor that just delivers directly into my hand.

679
00:45:09,180 --> 00:45:13,160
Wow, I didn't get to taste this in a long time.

680
00:45:13,160 --> 00:45:16,030
Hyungnim, we need to starve...

681
00:45:16,030 --> 00:45:19,300
in order for the people not to starve.

682
00:45:19,300 --> 00:45:21,400
Once we get our bellies full of fat...

683
00:45:21,400 --> 00:45:24,240
that's when the people starve.

684
00:45:24,240 --> 00:45:28,810
They'll starve because their brains don't get any truth, all right?

685
00:45:28,810 --> 00:45:32,000
By the way, why did you want to meet him?

686
00:45:32,000 --> 00:45:34,230
It's not even a film magazine.

687
00:45:34,230 --> 00:45:37,390
Could we buy this company from you?

688
00:45:37,390 --> 00:45:38,530
We'll hire more reporters and

689
00:45:38,530 --> 00:45:40,470
also print more than enough volumes.

690
00:45:40,470 --> 00:45:42,900
And you can keep your position as the CEO.

691
00:45:42,900 --> 00:45:44,500
Sorry?

692
00:45:45,500 --> 00:45:49,490
Why buy such a puny magazine company like ours?

693
00:45:49,490 --> 00:45:51,370
It won't be puny anymore.

694
00:45:51,370 --> 00:45:54,100
I'm sorry! I'm sorry, Sunbaenim.

695
00:45:54,100 --> 00:45:55,710
For what?

696
00:45:55,710 --> 00:45:58,120
For trying to get insured.

697
00:45:59,120 --> 00:46:00,770
That's right, you punk.

698
00:46:00,770 --> 00:46:03,250
You came to the wrong person!

699
00:46:03,250 --> 00:46:04,950
Stand up.

700
00:46:08,590 --> 00:46:10,240
Sit down.

701
00:46:16,210 --> 00:46:20,390
Even if my sword is in pieces like a rusty saw...

702
00:46:20,390 --> 00:46:23,140
I can still take down someone like you.

703
00:46:23,140 --> 00:46:26,820
And how much will it hurt when you get slashed by a sword that's rusty and old,

704
00:46:26,820 --> 00:46:29,690
which won't even go in smoothly?

705
00:46:29,690 --> 00:46:31,620
It'll hurt two or three times worse, right?

706
00:46:31,620 --> 00:46:34,380
- Yes.
- Also, man...

707
00:46:34,380 --> 00:46:36,940
if you're going to do a background search, do it right.

708
00:46:36,940 --> 00:46:39,590
A house on annual lease, too small for my family?

709
00:46:39,590 --> 00:46:42,300
Gosh, this asshole!

710
00:46:42,300 --> 00:46:45,010
I even gave all of that to my wife.

711
00:46:45,010 --> 00:46:46,890
She divorced me a week ago!

712
00:46:46,890 --> 00:46:50,360
I'm a prosecutor, who's got jack shit! All right?

713
00:46:50,360 --> 00:46:52,480
I have nothing to lose right now

714
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:54,160
and nothing to fear, either!

715
00:46:54,160 --> 00:46:57,620
Then you just went ahead and put salt...

716
00:46:57,620 --> 00:47:00,120
on my wounded pride.

717
00:47:00,120 --> 00:47:02,040
Do you think you were wrong...

718
00:47:02,040 --> 00:47:04,030
or not?

719
00:47:04,030 --> 00:47:05,920
I was wrong.

720
00:47:05,920 --> 00:47:07,720
[Prosecutor Kim Sung Yeob]

721
00:47:07,720 --> 00:47:08,920
Thank you for the trouble.

722
00:47:08,920 --> 00:47:10,800
Hey, he's got quite the slaps.

723
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:12,570
My back tooth is still shaky.

724
00:47:12,570 --> 00:47:14,780
Anyhow, we can say he passed the test.

725
00:47:14,780 --> 00:47:17,090
You said he used to be in the Special Investigations, right?

726
00:47:17,090 --> 00:47:18,530
Yes.

727
00:47:18,530 --> 00:47:20,130
Will you send the documents?

728
00:47:20,130 --> 00:47:23,750
We'll first send the copy and get him back in Seoul.

729
00:47:23,750 --> 00:47:26,150
All right. I'll ask the chief prosecutor.

730
00:47:26,150 --> 00:47:29,230
Don't we also need to find a trustworthy journalist?

731
00:47:29,230 --> 00:47:31,340
I'm already looking.

732
00:47:31,340 --> 00:47:33,230
Prosecutor Kim, you've got a delivery.

733
00:47:34,230 --> 00:47:35,810
Prosecutor Kim...

734
00:47:36,720 --> 00:47:39,290
- Prosecutor Kim!
- Wh-What? What is it?

735
00:47:39,290 --> 00:47:40,400
You've got mail.

736
00:47:40,400 --> 00:47:43,300
- Oh, thank you.
- Sure.

737
00:47:43,300 --> 00:47:44,400
[From: No Sook Ja*, 43-205 Dongja-dong, Yongsan-gu, Seoul-si]
