752
00:48:30,190 --> 00:48:33,850
I'm not playing around, and we'll meet eventually.

753
00:48:33,850 --> 00:48:37,430
I'll give you the original then, so keep that in a safe place for now.

754
00:48:37,430 --> 00:48:39,190
Do you know what you're doing right—

755
00:48:39,190 --> 00:48:41,530
Hello? Hello?

756
00:48:41,530 --> 00:48:43,540
What's up with this asshole?

757
00:48:51,490 --> 00:48:53,920
What do you think you're doing?

758
00:48:53,920 --> 00:48:57,330
Aigoo, Gramps, please talk it out.

759
00:48:57,330 --> 00:49:00,910
I sent you back here to do my business.

760
00:49:00,910 --> 00:49:03,150
I didn't do it to tend to your business!

761
00:49:03,150 --> 00:49:05,510
What are you so angry about right now?

762
00:49:05,510 --> 00:49:08,060
I didn't mess up any of your business.

763
00:49:08,060 --> 00:49:11,450
Doo Hak, what's going on with Changsung Constructions?

764
00:49:11,450 --> 00:49:12,900
What's the problem with them?

765
00:49:12,900 --> 00:49:14,460
You really don't know?

766
00:49:14,460 --> 00:49:16,750
You're a pathetic idiot if you didn't know!

767
00:49:16,750 --> 00:49:19,060
Didn't you say Changsung Constructions will go bankrupt?

768
00:49:19,060 --> 00:49:20,390
However...

769
00:49:20,390 --> 00:49:24,000
they'll be building a large apartment complex in a place called Sooseo District.

770
00:49:24,000 --> 00:49:27,160
So did Chansung Constructions build those apartments already?

771
00:49:27,160 --> 00:49:28,800
The rumor is already widespread.

772
00:49:28,800 --> 00:49:30,650
There will be an official announcement soon.

773
00:49:30,650 --> 00:49:34,040
Their stock price already rose 30% and will rise even more from now on.

774
00:49:34,040 --> 00:49:35,820
How could you say that company will go bankrupt?

775
00:49:35,820 --> 00:49:38,350
While waiting for Changsung Constructions...

776
00:49:38,350 --> 00:49:41,950
I had to let go of a number of great companies!

777
00:49:42,950 --> 00:49:46,180
You're causing this scene over something like that?

778
00:49:46,180 --> 00:49:47,800
What?

779
00:49:58,160 --> 00:49:59,870
That's great.

780
00:49:59,870 --> 00:50:02,690
The rumor's up and about and the stock price went up.

781
00:50:02,690 --> 00:50:05,290
What are you talking about? Explain so we can understand.

782
00:50:05,290 --> 00:50:09,300
If they go bankrupt while getting the entire nation's attention...

783
00:50:09,300 --> 00:50:11,920
it'll be easier to buy than scrap iron.

784
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:13,990
Even I can understand that...

785
00:50:13,990 --> 00:50:17,530
but why are you saying Changsung Constructions will go bankrupt?

786
00:50:17,530 --> 00:50:19,710
Because I'll make them go bankrupt.

787
00:50:19,710 --> 00:50:21,020
By what means?

788
00:50:21,020 --> 00:50:23,050
I can't tell you that right now.

789
00:50:23,050 --> 00:50:24,390
Weren't we all one family?

790
00:50:24,400 --> 00:50:28,500
I've never seen a family who throws an ashtray before getting the result.

791
00:50:28,530 --> 00:50:30,430
Hey, Fish...

792
00:50:30,430 --> 00:50:33,410
Can you take responsibility?

793
00:50:33,410 --> 00:50:36,770
If you fail on this one, I'll report you!

794
00:50:37,770 --> 00:50:40,220
It's clear we're not family.

795
00:50:41,220 --> 00:50:43,510
If you just wait a bit longer...

796
00:50:43,510 --> 00:50:47,510
I'll bring you the news of victory.

797
00:50:47,510 --> 00:50:49,660
I'm going.

798
00:50:49,660 --> 00:50:53,130
What's that punk saying he'll do right now?

799
00:50:56,850 --> 00:50:59,090
Pardon me. Are you enjoying your food?

800
00:50:59,090 --> 00:51:00,950
Yes, it's delicious.

801
00:51:00,950 --> 00:51:02,270
Sorry?

802
00:51:02,270 --> 00:51:04,830
You're going to sell the building in Apgujeong?

803
00:51:04,830 --> 00:51:08,830
That 15 story building, the cream of the crop?

804
00:51:08,830 --> 00:51:12,930
Yes, I'd like to have it sold as soon as possible, Accountant Yang.

805
00:51:12,930 --> 00:51:15,680
Well, it's already valued at more than 15 billion won and

806
00:51:15,680 --> 00:51:18,040
it'll even exceed 20 billion won soon enough.

807
00:51:18,040 --> 00:51:19,830
Isn't that too much of a waste?

808
00:51:19,830 --> 00:51:21,730
Do you think I don't see that?

809
00:51:21,730 --> 00:51:23,230
But what can I do?

810
00:51:23,300 --> 00:51:28,500
I can't let my only son get locked up after bankrupting his company!

811
00:51:28,560 --> 00:51:31,950
If you want to sell it in a rush, how much do you want for it?

812
00:51:31,950 --> 00:51:34,230
I'll sell it at about 12 billion won.

813
00:51:34,230 --> 00:51:35,420
Sorry?

814
00:51:35,420 --> 00:51:39,840
Madam, I think that's way too cheap.

815
00:51:39,840 --> 00:51:44,440
My son will die if we can't pay the loan within a month!

816
00:51:44,440 --> 00:51:47,130
Hello. Are you enjoying your steaks?

817
00:51:47,130 --> 00:51:49,880
Oh, yes. They're very tender and delicious.

818
00:51:49,880 --> 00:51:53,490
I can't tell if this meat is going...

819
00:51:53,490 --> 00:51:55,510
into my mouth or my nose.

820
00:51:55,510 --> 00:52:00,300
I'm sure people will line up to purchase it at that price.

821
00:52:00,300 --> 00:52:02,180
I'm sorry for raising my voice.

822
00:52:02,180 --> 00:52:03,870
No, not at all.

823
00:52:03,870 --> 00:52:07,590
Right. When we get a new wine at our salon,

824
00:52:07,590 --> 00:52:10,900
we invite only the VIPs for wine tasting.

825
00:52:10,900 --> 00:52:13,450
If you give me your business cards, I'll contact you.

826
00:52:13,450 --> 00:52:15,350
Wine sounds great.

827
00:52:15,350 --> 00:52:16,950
One moment, please.

828
00:52:17,950 --> 00:52:19,320
Here you go.

829
00:52:20,370 --> 00:52:21,620
[Principal CPA Yang Sung Geun, AGJ Tax & Accounting]

830
00:52:22,530 --> 00:52:25,160
Oh, you're a CPA?

831
00:52:25,160 --> 00:52:26,390
Well, yes.

832
00:52:26,390 --> 00:52:28,290
Okay, I'll be sure to give you a call.

833
00:52:28,290 --> 00:52:30,260
Please enjoy your meal.

834
00:52:31,950 --> 00:52:34,740
Gosh, the thing is really...

835
00:52:46,230 --> 00:52:47,820
A little bit toward that way...

836
00:52:51,480 --> 00:52:53,730
Hey, let's get out of here! Quickly!

837
00:52:53,730 --> 00:52:55,240
- Hurry up!
- Quickly!

838
00:52:55,240 --> 00:52:58,250
Did you let it slip naturally? Huh?

839
00:52:59,570 --> 00:53:03,770
Aigoo! Hey, I almost died of a heart attack!

840
00:53:03,770 --> 00:53:07,150
I almost lost my own eyes from trying to pluck her eyeballs.

841
00:53:07,200 --> 00:53:11,050
I had to watch her, but my limbs were trembling, and I almost spoke in my dialect.

842
00:53:11,050 --> 00:53:12,840
I was really at my wit's end.

843
00:53:12,840 --> 00:53:15,190
Hey, why aren't you starting the car? Let's get out of here!

844
00:53:15,190 --> 00:53:17,840
This shitty car isn't starting! What can I do!

845
00:53:17,840 --> 00:53:20,720
You were talking about Jo Se Hyeong and Hwalbindang*,
(Famous thieves in Korean history)

846
00:53:20,720 --> 00:53:23,890
but you can never be a big thief, Hyungnim.

847
00:53:23,890 --> 00:53:28,240
Hey, man, we're trying to pluck NSA Deputy Director's wife's eyeballs here!

848
00:53:28,240 --> 00:53:32,350
Even Jo Se Hyeong, Hong Gil Dong*, and Lim Kkeok Jung* would get scared!
(Robin Hood figures in Korean history)

849
00:53:32,350 --> 00:53:33,810
Gosh, all right.

850
00:53:33,810 --> 00:53:37,290
Anyhow, I hope they bite the bait nice and hard.

851
00:53:37,290 --> 00:53:40,040
Seeing how her ears were sharp while pretending not to listen,

852
00:53:40,040 --> 00:53:43,120
I think she'll bite it 100%, probably.

853
00:53:43,120 --> 00:53:45,280
Hey, so let's be very cautious. Okay?

854
00:53:45,280 --> 00:53:47,310
With one wrong step,

855
00:53:47,310 --> 00:53:51,240
forget prison sentence. we'll be torn limb by limb.

856
00:53:51,240 --> 00:53:54,070
- <i>Whoa! It started!</i>
- Hey, step on it!

857
00:53:54,070 --> 00:53:57,030
Let's go!

858
00:54:00,630 --> 00:54:02,370
Welcome.

859
00:54:10,730 --> 00:54:13,750
Your mom wanted to have lunch since there's a new head chef.

860
00:54:13,750 --> 00:54:16,030
Let's all give our opinions.

861
00:54:16,030 --> 00:54:17,740
Okay.

862
00:54:17,740 --> 00:54:22,370
You're troubled lately because of CEO Oh Jung Shin, right?

863
00:54:22,370 --> 00:54:25,130
I told him about her.

864
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:29,940
Why don't you go to a branch in the U.S. or Europe to take a breather?

865
00:54:30,960 --> 00:54:32,970
No.

866
00:54:32,970 --> 00:54:36,350
I don't want to run away for a reason like that.

867
00:54:36,350 --> 00:54:39,250
I'll stay here, Father.

868
00:54:39,250 --> 00:54:43,710
All right. If you can face it and overcome it, that's better.

869
00:54:51,390 --> 00:54:54,660
Here's your clam chowder in bread bowl.

870
00:54:57,420 --> 00:54:59,170
Long time no see, sir.

871
00:54:59,170 --> 00:55:01,170
She's our special head chef for the day.

872
00:55:01,170 --> 00:55:04,950
She wanted our family to try the food she learned to make in the U.S.

873
00:55:04,950 --> 00:55:06,170
Yes.

874
00:55:06,170 --> 00:55:09,530
Please try some and let me know how it is.

875
00:55:13,230 --> 00:55:15,050
It's flavorful and delicious.

876
00:55:15,050 --> 00:55:16,910
What about you, Dear?

877
00:55:18,160 --> 00:55:22,310
I think I'll have to make this our salon's signature menu.

878
00:55:23,860 --> 00:55:25,200
Why don't you try some, sir?

879
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:27,420
Do you like me that much?

880
00:55:29,120 --> 00:55:31,850
You like to cut to the chase.

881
00:55:31,850 --> 00:55:34,120
Yes, I do.

882
00:55:34,120 --> 00:55:37,080
Enough to treat you to a dish I spent two hours on.

883
00:55:37,080 --> 00:55:38,530
Thank you.

884
00:55:38,530 --> 00:55:40,400
I'll enjoy the food.

885
00:55:41,950 --> 00:55:43,590
By the way...

886
00:55:43,590 --> 00:55:46,140
there's a woman I've been working on for 10 years.

887
00:55:46,140 --> 00:55:49,770
But she hurt me recently, so my heart is aching too much right now.

888
00:55:49,770 --> 00:55:53,400
So, since I don't want to hurt your feelings,

889
00:55:53,400 --> 00:55:56,530
I'll enjoy today's food, at the very least.

890
00:55:57,550 --> 00:55:59,200
Thank you.

891
00:56:15,240 --> 00:56:17,700
You know, when you look in history,

892
00:56:17,700 --> 00:56:20,220
neighboring countries exchanged prisoners,

893
00:56:20,220 --> 00:56:23,520
formed marriages of convenience and stuff, right?

894
00:56:23,520 --> 00:56:25,610
They say they'll send their princess for the marriage,

895
00:56:25,610 --> 00:56:29,250
but send a commoner woman to the neighboring country instead.

896
00:56:29,250 --> 00:56:34,490
In fact, that was my purpose in approaching you, too.

897
00:56:34,490 --> 00:56:39,530
So my father and his company can approach Deputy Director and his wife...

898
00:56:39,530 --> 00:56:41,680
I had to make my move.

899
00:56:42,680 --> 00:56:45,920
Saying stuff like how I said I liked you...

900
00:56:46,920 --> 00:56:49,460
although it wasn't completely false...

901
00:56:49,460 --> 00:56:51,060
it was all just a show.

902
00:56:51,060 --> 00:56:53,860
But a few days ago, Father told me this.

903
00:56:53,860 --> 00:56:57,880
He got to know Madam and got into a business together.

904
00:56:57,880 --> 00:57:01,950
So I can stop putting on a show.

905
00:57:02,950 --> 00:57:07,280
I apologize for acting in front of you, although it wasn't my intention.

906
00:57:08,500 --> 00:57:13,200
It's okay since I wasn't that serious of an audience.

907
00:57:16,280 --> 00:57:19,900
CEO Oh Jung Shin who runs a film studio.

908
00:57:20,900 --> 00:57:25,950
I already knew you had her in your heart before I started all this.

909
00:57:25,950 --> 00:57:27,580
Nonetheless,

910
00:57:27,580 --> 00:57:33,070
we also have a department that looks up all kinds of information for no reason.

911
00:57:33,070 --> 00:57:34,650
So, let me apologize, but...

912
00:57:34,650 --> 00:57:38,550
we also looked into CEO Oh Jung Shin's surroundings.

913
00:57:38,550 --> 00:57:42,360
The guys who kept a watch around CEO Oh's house

914
00:57:42,360 --> 00:57:45,190
told me an interesting story a few days ago.

915
00:57:46,590 --> 00:57:49,830
It looks like she's in love with someone.

916
00:57:53,180 --> 00:57:55,530
A certain man appeared...

917
00:57:55,530 --> 00:57:59,460
around CEO Oh's house, one late night.

918
00:58:01,450 --> 00:58:04,000
CEO Oh and that man...

919
00:58:04,000 --> 00:58:06,930
hugged each other in joy and cried for hours...

920
00:58:06,960 --> 00:58:12,000
as if they were loves who have been apart for years.

921
00:58:14,170 --> 00:58:16,660
I didn't know if I wanted to tell you this or not.

922
00:58:16,660 --> 00:58:20,040
But your face looked too lonely earlier.

923
00:58:20,040 --> 00:58:21,700
All right, then.

924
00:58:30,950 --> 00:58:32,430
The preparations are complete.

925
00:58:32,430 --> 00:58:35,080
I'm the publisher of that magazine starting this month.

926
00:58:35,080 --> 00:58:36,720
<i>Let's meet up and talk.</i>

927
00:58:36,720 --> 00:58:38,520
<i>Thank you for the work.</i>

928
00:58:38,520 --> 00:58:41,760
<i>I had something to tell you anyway, so it's great timing.</i>

929
00:58:41,760 --> 00:58:43,610
I'll buy you dinner today.

930
00:58:43,610 --> 00:58:45,850
<i>Buy me something expensive, all right?</i>

931
00:58:46,890 --> 00:58:48,380
[NSA Deputy Director's Special Aide, Choi Cheol Woong]

932
00:59:52,000 --> 00:59:56,780
♫ <i>Can't you hear me?</i> ♫

933
00:59:58,990 --> 01:00:04,690
♫ <i>You still linger around my ears</i> ♫

934
01:00:04,690 --> 01:00:11,390
♫ <i>I close my eyes again and take a deep breath</i> ♫

935
01:00:11,390 --> 01:00:18,490
♫ <i>I count the moments we'll meet again</i> ♫

936
01:00:18,490 --> 01:00:23,960
♫ <i>I hold you up among the waves</i> ♫

937
01:00:25,570 --> 01:00:30,860
♫ <i>You fill me, who is always winding</i> ♫

938
01:00:32,510 --> 01:00:39,220
♫ <i>On the dusty road, you're my only breath</i> ♫

939
01:00:39,220 --> 01:00:44,400
♫ <i>Will you breeze by from time to time?</i> ♫

940
01:00:44,400 --> 01:00:47,200
[Oasis]

941
01:00:47,200 --> 01:00:50,100
<i>Please be my Princess Pyeonggang*. I'll make it up to you for the rest of my life.</i>
(Historical figure)

942
01:00:50,100 --> 01:00:52,690
<i>I just can't bare to watch you become miserable.</i>

943
01:00:52,690 --> 01:00:53,520
<i>Hey, Choi Cheol Woong.</i>

944
01:00:53,520 --> 01:00:55,150
<i>Of all people, you can't do this to me.</i>

945
01:00:55,150 --> 01:00:57,340
- <i>Cheol Woong...
- You can't have Jung Shin.</i>

946
01:00:57,340 --> 01:00:58,820
<i>Cheol Woong!</i>

947
01:00:58,820 --> 01:01:02,090
<i>Cheol Woong might be completely ruined when the trigger is pulled.</i>

948
01:01:02,090 --> 01:01:05,190
<i>I heard you did it, huh? At Yeosu...</i>

949
01:01:05,200 --> 01:01:08,160
<i>Why? Are you frustrated that I didn't die?</i>

950
01:01:08,160 --> 01:01:10,560
<i>- Yeah, bastard.
- Want me to tell you a funny story?</i>

951
01:01:10,560 --> 01:01:12,150
<i>Choi Cheol Woong's birth father is...</i>

952
01:01:12,150 --> 01:01:13,870
<i>I knew it as well.</i>

953
01:01:13,870 --> 01:01:16,830
<i>Yeo Jin must've had it tough because of you, Team Captain Oh.</i>

954
01:01:16,830 --> 01:01:17,730
<i>Commander.</i>

955
01:01:17,730 --> 01:01:19,680
<i>I'll have someone else watch Lee Doo Hak.</i>

956
01:01:19,700 --> 01:01:22,500
<i>- No, I'll put an end to Lee Doo Hak—
- I told you to stop!</i>

957
01:01:22,500 --> 01:01:24,940
<i>People still don't know what kind of person Lee Doo Hak is.</i>

958
01:01:25,000 --> 01:01:28,000
<i>- Are you sure you can beat me?
- I won't lose on purpose.</i>

959
01:01:28,060 --> 01:01:32,060
♫ <i>I hold you up among the waves</i> ♫

